[start section id="20112"]

#1 Colon cancer, grade 3 (out of 4) adenocarcinoma
#2 Emphysema
As Mr. Blom's colonoscopy was incomplete as they could not go past the splenic flexure due to the mass, we will proceed with a repeat colonoscopy to try to assess the proximal colon, and if that is unsuccessful, he will go on to CT colonography.  Also, complete the colorectal cancer staging evaluation including basic laboratory workup, CEA, a CT of the chest, abdomen, and pelvis.  We will also proceed with PFTs since he has a history of extensive smoking and personal history of emphysema.
#3 Dysphagia
Patient has reported dysphagia in the last few weeks with a pill he has taken for the last few years.  However, he denies any solid or liquid dysphagia, so with that, we will proceed with an EGD.  Of note, he has not taken his aspirin for several weeks.
#4 Personal history of a lung nodule
Patient reports that he has a history of a lung nodule that is unremarkable and has been worked-up in the past in New Jersey by pulmonologists.  This will be seen on chest CT most likely.  The above was discussed with Ms. Shaw and Dr. Fenley, and they agree with what is discussed above.
ADVANCE DIRECTIVES
Advance directive or living will: Yes, not on file at Carthage Hospital Center.

