[start section id="20103"]

Mr. Blom is a 77-year-old male with a recent diagnosis of grade 3 (out of 4) adenocarcinoma of the colon at the splenic flexure and is here for further evaluation.  Mr. Blom has been suffering from anorexia, fatigue, and weight-loss over the last year.  He reports that he has lost about 15 pounds.  When he went in for evaluation in May of 2010, they noted he had anemia with a hemoglobin of 9.9, but none of his other lab work was grossly abnormal.  He went for a colonoscopy, which was done June 11, 2010, and this revealed a partially obstructing mass at the splenic flexure as well as diverticulosis.  Pathology was reviewed here and revealed invasive grade 3 (out of 4) adenocarcinoma.  He denies any melena, hematochezia, nausea, vomiting, fevers, chills, night sweats, or other symptoms unless previously noted.

[end section id="20103"]

